<a name="XCBConnect" id="XCBConnect"></a>

## XCBConnect

(xcb\_util.c %P%)

`XCBConnection *XCBConnect(const char *display, int *screen)`

Connects to the X server specified by `display`. If `display` is null, uses the value of the DISPLAY environment variable. If a particular screen on that server is preferred, the int pointed to by `screen` (if non-null) will be set to that screen; otherwise the screen will be set to 0.

Calls:

- [XCBGetFDFromDisplay](http://xcb.freedesktop.org/wiki/)
- [XCBGetAuthInfo](http://xcb.freedesktop.org/wiki/)
- [XCBConnectToFD](http://xcb.freedesktop.org/wiki/)

<a name="XCBConnectToDisplayWithAuthInfo" id="XCBConnectToDisplayWithAuthInfo"></a>

## XCBConnectToDisplayWithAuthInfo

(xcb\_util.c %P%)

`XCBConnection *XCBConnectToDisplayWithAuthInfo(const char *display, XCBAuthInfo *auth, int *screen)`

Connects to the X server specified by `display`, using the given authorization information. If a particular screen on that server is preferred, the int pointed to by `screen` (if non-null) will be set to that screen; otherwise the screen will be set to 0.

Calls:

- [XCBGetFDFromDisplay](http://xcb.freedesktop.org/wiki/)
- [XCBConnectToFD](http://xcb.freedesktop.org/wiki/)

<a name="XCBConnectToDD" id="XCBConnectToDD"></a>

## XCBConnectToFD

(xcb\_conn.c %P%)

`XCBConnection *XCBConnectToFD(int fd, XCBAuthInfo *auth_info)`

Connects to an X server, given an open socket and a suitable [XCBAuthInfo](http://xcb.freedesktop.org/wiki/).

<dl>
  <dt>fd</dt>
  <dd>
    <p>a file descriptor bidirectionally connected to an X server. <a href="http://xcb.freedesktop.org/wiki/">XCBGetTCPFD</a> and <a href="http://xcb.freedesktop.org/wiki/">XCBGetUnixFD</a> return appropriate file descriptors.</p>
  </dd>
  <dt>auth_info</dt>
  <dd>
    <p>authentication data, or 0 if the connection should be unauthenticated. <a href="http://xcb.freedesktop.org/wiki/">XCBGetAuthInfo</a> returns appropriate authentication data.</p>
  </dd>
  <dt>Returns</dt>
  <dd>
    <p>an <a href="http://xcb.freedesktop.org/wiki/">XCBConnection</a>, or 0 on failure.</p>
  </dd>
</dl>

See also [XCBConnect](http://xcb.freedesktop.org/wiki/).

